issue.body:
```c++
int foo(int x) {
    return x >= 0 ? x % 16 : 42;
}
```

This is equivalent to `x >= 0 ? x & 15 : 42`.

However, clang 14.0.0 compiles this to something like:
`x >= 0 ? x - ((x >= 0 ? x : x + 15) & -16) : 42`

Note that the second `x >= 0` is completely redundant.

https://godbolt.org/z/4Ee3sbbWs
